      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/63/1",
      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا إِبْرَاهِيمَ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ زِيَارَةِ اَلْبَيْتِ تُؤَخَّرُ إِلَى يَوْمِ اَلثَّالِثِ فَقَالَ «تَعْجِيلُهَا أَحَبُّ إِلَيَّ وَ لَيْسَ بِهِ بَأْسٌ إِنْ أَخَّرْتَهُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2781 - It is narrated from Ishaq ibn Ammar, who said: I asked Abu Ibrahim (as) about delaying the visitation of the Kaaba (Tawaf al-Ziyara) until the third day.\nImam (as) said: \"Performing it earlier is more beloved to me, but there is no harm if you delay it.\""
        ]
      }
    },
